#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.108"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.108:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.108:0.2"
msgid "11. Valāhakavagga "
msgstr "11. Clouds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: balivaddasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.108:0.3"
msgid "108. Balībaddasutta "
msgstr "108. Oxen "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.109, sc1
#. VAR: balībaddā → balivaddā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | balibaddhā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.108:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, balībaddā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of oxen. "

msgctxt "an4.108:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.108:1.3"
msgid "Sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo, paragavacaṇḍo no sagavacaṇḍo, sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca, neva sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo—"
msgstr "~One hostile to its own herd, not others; ~one hostile to other herds, not its own; ~one hostile to both its own herd and others; and ~one hostile to neither its own herd nor others. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
msgctxt "an4.108:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddā. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of oxen. "

msgctxt "an4.108:1.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, these four people similar to oxen are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.108:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.108:1.7"
msgid "Sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo, paragavacaṇḍo no sagavacaṇḍo, sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca, neva sagavacaṇḍo no paragavacaṇḍo. "
msgstr "~One hostile to their own herd, not others; ~one hostile to other herds, not their own; ~one hostile to both their own herd and others; and ~one hostile to neither their own herd nor others. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.108:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo? "
msgstr "And how is a person hostile to their own herd, not others? "

msgctxt "an4.108:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no paraparisaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person intimidates their own followers, not the followers of others. "

msgctxt "an4.108:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is hostile to their own herd, not others. "

msgctxt "an4.108:2.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo sagavacaṇḍo, no paragavacaṇḍo; "
msgstr "That person is like an ox that’s hostile to its own herd, not others. "

msgctxt "an4.108:2.5"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.108:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo paragavacaṇḍo hoti, no sagavacaṇḍo? "
msgstr "And how is a person hostile to other herds, not their own? "

msgctxt "an4.108:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo paraparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no sakaparisaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a person intimidates the followers of others, not their own. … "

msgctxt "an4.108:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo paragavacaṇḍo hoti, no sagavacaṇḍo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:3.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo paragavacaṇḍo, no sagavacaṇḍo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:3.5"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.108:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo ca hoti paragavacaṇḍo ca? "
msgstr "And how is a person hostile to both their own herd and others? "

msgctxt "an4.108:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti paraparisañca. "
msgstr "It’s when a person intimidates their own followers and the followers of others. … "

msgctxt "an4.108:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo sagavacaṇḍo ca hoti paragavacaṇḍo ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:4.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo sagavacaṇḍo ca paragavacaṇḍo ca; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:4.5"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.108:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva sagavacaṇḍo hoti no paragavacaṇḍo? "
msgstr "And how is a person hostile to neither their own herd nor others? "

msgctxt "an4.108:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo neva sakaparisaṃ ubbejetā hoti, no paraparisañca. "
msgstr "It’s when a person doesn’t intimidate their own followers or the followers of others. "

msgctxt "an4.108:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva sagavacaṇḍo hoti, no paragavacaṇḍo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:5.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, balībaddo neva sagavacaṇḍo, no paragavacaṇḍo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.108:5.5"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.108:5.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro balībaddūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These four people similar to oxen are found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.108:5.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

